pedrambiria (Issue Creator) on (2025-01-08 10:41:45 UTC): @davidmonnom when we delete an order, we do not remove it from the server; instead, we mark it as canceled. Also, based on the function name `localDeleteCascade`, it seems the intention was to delete it only locally. If you believe we need to change this logic, I can modify it to remove the order from the server and also rename the function accordingly. What do you think?

davidmonnom on (2025-01-08 12:39:01 UTC): In this case, we'd have to change the check in this method to accept the local delete only when the order is cancel or not yet synced.

```js
        if (typeof record.id === "number" && !force) {
            console.info(
                `Record ID ${record.id} MODEL ${recordModel}. If you want to delete a record saved on the server, you need to pass the force parameter as true.`
            );
            return;
        }
```

pedrambiria (Issue Creator) on (2025-01-09 10:11:24 UTC): @davidmonnom I modified the code. I replaced the `force` parameter with `removeFromServer` and set it to `false` when canceling an order. Additionally, I noticed that releasing a table did not update immediately, so I added a debounced `syncAllOrders` call in the `removeOrder` method to ensure timely updates.
